Alembic migrations for the Investment Co-Pilot's Postgres database.

WHEN THIS APPLIES
  SQLite (local dev + tests) uses SQLAlchemy create_all — Alembic is not needed
  there. Alembic manages the *Postgres* schema (Supabase). The connection URL is
  read from DATABASE_URL by env.py (same as the app), so no URL lives in
  alembic.ini.

CHANGING THE SCHEMA
  1. Edit the models in db/models.py.
  2. Autogenerate a revision (with DATABASE_URL pointed at Postgres):
       python -m alembic revision --autogenerate -m "what changed"
  3. READ the generated file in alembic/versions/ — autogenerate is a draft.
     It does NOT capture the Row-Level Security policies (those live in
     db/session.py:_apply_postgres_rls and are (re)applied idempotently on
     startup); if a change needs new RLS, add it to that function too.
  4. Apply it:
       python -m alembic upgrade head
  5. Sanity check there's no drift left:
       python -m alembic check          # -> "No new upgrade operations detected."

FRESH POSTGRES DEPLOY
  Either run `python -m alembic upgrade head` before first app start, OR just
  start the app: init_db() calls create_all and then auto-stamps the baseline
  (db/session.py:_ensure_alembic_stamp), so later `alembic upgrade head` applies
  only NEW revisions.

REVISION HISTORY
  5d7e93f6a306  initial baseline schema (full table set). The live Supabase DB
                was created via create_all and `alembic stamp`-ed to this.
  f6ce2dbad4ac  user_id NOT NULL on the 7 user-owned tables (backfills legacy
                NULLs to the bootstrap owner first).
